Name: Cipher
Desc: In the fallen city of bandits, Dolos, the 300 Rogues run wild and free, the entire city at their mercy.\nRace onward, fleet-Footed Thief Star Cifera, Chrysos Heir of the "Trickery" Coreflame, and may your web of lies spread with the breeze throughout all landsâ€”\n"Tryna trick me? Fetch better scripts!"

1.Name: Read the Room, Seek the Glee
1.Desc: Cipher's recorded DMG is <unbreak>#3[i]%</unbreak> of the original recorded DMG value. When using a <u>Follow-up ATK</u> caused by her Talent, increases Cipher's ATK by <unbreak>#1[i]%</unbreak> for <unbreak>#2[i]</unbreak> turn(s).

2.Name: In the Fray, Nab On a Spree
2.Desc: When Cipher hits an enemy target, there is a <unbreak>#2[i]%</unbreak> <u>base chance</u> of causing them to receive <unbreak>#3[i]%</unbreak> more DMG, lasting <unbreak>#1[i]</unbreak> turn(s).

3.Name: From Thin Air, Hard to Foresee
3.Desc: Ultimate Lv. +2, up to a maximum of Lv. <unbreak>15</unbreak>.\nBasic ATK Lv. +1, up to a maximum of Lv. <unbreak>10</unbreak>.

4.Name: The Jig Is Up, Quick to Flee
4.Desc: After "Patron" is attacked by an ally target, Cipher deals Quantum <u>Additional DMG</u> equal to <unbreak>#1[i]%</unbreak> of Cipher's ATK to it.

5.Name: Safe in Numbers, Light as a Bee
5.Desc: Skill Lv. +2, up to a maximum of Lv. <unbreak>15</unbreak>.\nTalent Lv. +2, up to a maximum of Lv. <unbreak>15</unbreak>.

6.Name: The Thief's Game, Unsung and Free
6.Desc: Increases DMG dealt by <u>Follow-up ATK</u>s caused by Cipher's Talent by <unbreak>#2[i]%</unbreak>. Records an additional <unbreak>#3[i]%</unbreak> of non-Overflow DMG dealt by this ATK. After resetting the record upon using her Ultimate, returns <unbreak>#1[i]%</unbreak> of the reset record.

140601.Name: Oops, a Missed Catch
140601.Desc: Deals Quantum DMG equal to <color=#f29e38ff><unbreak>#1[i]%</unbreak></color> of Cipher's ATK to one designated enemy.

140602.Name: Hey, Jackpot for the Taking
140602.Desc: There is a <unbreak>#6[i]%</unbreak> <u>base chance</u> to Weaken one designated enemy and adjacent targets, decreasing their DMG dealt by <unbreak>#3[i]%</unbreak> and increasing Cipher's ATK by <unbreak>#5[i]%</unbreak>, lasting for <unbreak>#4[i]</unbreak> turn(s). At the same time, deals Quantum DMG equal to <color=#f29e38ff><unbreak>#1[i]%</unbreak></color> of Cipher's ATK to one designated enemy, and Quantum DMG equal to <color=#f29e38ff><unbreak>#2[i]%</unbreak></color> of Cipher's ATK to its adjacent targets.

140603.Name: Yours Truly, <unbreak>Kitty Phantom Thief!</unbreak>
140603.Desc: Deals Quantum DMG equal to <color=#f29e38ff><unbreak>#1[i]%</unbreak></color> of Cipher's ATK to one designated enemy. Then, deals <u>True DMG</u> equal to <unbreak>#2[i]%</unbreak> of the currently recorded Talent value to one designated enemy, Quantum DMG equal to <color=#f29e38ff><unbreak>#4[i]%</unbreak></color> of Cipher's ATK to one designated enemy and its adjacent targets, and <u>True DMG</u> equal to <unbreak>#3[i]%</unbreak> of the current Talent's recorded value. This <u>True DMG</u> is Distributed to all Skill targets.

140604.Name: The Hospitable Dolosian
140604.Desc: When there are no enemy targets in "Patron" state on the battlefield, Cipher immediately causes one enemy target with the highest Max HP on the battlefield to become the "Patron." When using Skill and Ultimate, the primary target becomes the "Patron." The "Patron" state only takes effect on the latest target.\nAfter the "Patron" is attacked by other ally targets, Cipher immediately launches a <u>Follow-up ATK</u> against the "Patron," dealing Quantum DMG equal to <color=#f29e38ff><unbreak>#1[i]%</unbreak></color> of Cipher's ATK. This effect can be triggered up to <unbreak>#3[i]</unbreak> time(s) each turn, and it resets at the start of Cipher's turn.\nCipher will record <unbreak>#2[i]%</unbreak> of the non-<u>True DMG</u> ally targets dealt to "Patron," but the Overflow DMG will not be recorded. The recorded value is cleared after using Ultimate.

140606.Name: Attack
140606.Desc: Attacks an enemy, and when the battle starts, reduces their Toughness of the corresponding Type.

140607.Name: Puss in Boots
140607.Desc: Obtains "Zagreus's Blessing" for <unbreak>#1[i]</unbreak> second(s). During this time, Cipher will be undetectable by enemies and her movement speed increases by <unbreak>50%</unbreak>. When approaching an enemy in the overworld/Simulated Universe/Divergent Universe, there is a chance of immediately obtaining a random Consumable. You can obtain Consumables up to <unbreak>#4[i]</unbreak> time(s) in each Earth day.\nWhen entering battle with "Zagreus's Blessing" active, deals Quantum DMG equal to <unbreak>#3[i]%</unbreak> of Cipher's ATK to all enemies. Increases the recorded DMG Cipher obtains from this instance of DMG by <unbreak>#2[i]%</unbreak>.

1.PointDesc: When Cipher's SPD is greater or equal to <unbreak>140</unbreak>/<unbreak>170</unbreak>, increases CRIT Rate by <unbreak>#1[i]%</unbreak>/<unbreak>#2[i]%</unbreak>, and recorded value by <unbreak>#3[i]%</unbreak>/<unbreak>#4[i]%</unbreak>.
Cipher will record <unbreak>#1[i]%</unbreak> of the non-<u>True DMG</u> ally targets dealt to the enemy targets aside from the "Patron." Overflow DMG is not recorded.

Increases the CRIT DMG dealt by the Talent's <u>Follow-up ATK</u> by <unbreak>#2[i]%</unbreak>. When Cipher is on the battlefield, DMG received by all enemy targets increases by <unbreak>#1[i]%</unbreak>.
